title: For Sale/Trade:  Remington 700, 7mm Rem Mag w/ KRG Whiskey 3 Chassis
postcontent:
I have for sale a very lightly used Remington 700 in 7mm RemMag.  I bought this from a friend who wanted to get into long range shooting and after not too long, decided it was not his game.  He shot 250 rounds through it, I shot 8 rounds through it with factory Hornady 139gr interlock, hunting ammo. I was able to shoot a 2" 5 shot group at 200 yds with that hunting ammo shooting prone, from the included bipod and a rear squeeze bag.  With good hand loads it should do even better than that.  The base rifle is a model 700 Long range, barrel is a 26" varmint contour 1 in 9.25 twist.  The factory stock was removed and the barreled action was dropped into a KRG whiskey 3 chassis.  Chassis is Aluminum with composite grip panels.  Has adjustable cheek rest both fore and aft, and vertically, and has adjustable LOP, and vertical adjustment of the butt plate.  The chassis also has built in QD sling mounts as well as a multitude of attachment points for picatinny rails on the fore end.  Uses AICS long actions magazines (none included).  I will include the bipod (appears to be a blackhawk), and I will ship the rifle in a fitted Plano tactical hard case.  The only thing I can find wrong with the whole gun is that the small screw in the face of the trigger seems to be missing.  I don't think this will affect safety or function of the trigger at all.  The only reason I am selling it is because I have no need for a 7mm Rem Mag, and I don't want to use a long action for my next project.  NOTE: The trigger in this rifle is an X-Mark Pro trigger, under Remington's Voluntary Recall.  It has not been sent in to be cleaned by Remington.  I recommend either replacing the trigger with an aftermarket, or sending the barreled action into Remington to be fixed under the recall.  The buyer of this rifle acknowledges this and assumes all responsibility for the trigger once received.

Rifle complete- $1300+ 75 for shipping
I will part out if I get a buyer for both the barreled action and the chassis.  Prices Separate will be:

Because the .22LR round is not copper jacketed, molten lead and carbon debris will explode into the silencer when the projectile exits the muzzle. After some time, it is possible for a .22 suppressor to fill completely with lead and become heavy and ineffective. To avoid this issue, .22 silencers must be disassembled for cleaning and regular maintenance. Until SilencerCo introduced the 22Sparrow, the only .22 silencers that could be disassembled for cleaning required a cleaning every 50 to 200 rounds. However, often the components of those silencers would be fused together and unable to come apart. Competitor products on the market have baffles in their .22 silencers that must be removed by twisting the outer tube around the baffles and/or sliding the outer tube off of the baffles. When the lead and carbon debris adhere to the inner wall of the outer tube and fill the spaces between the baffles and the outer tube, there is simply too much buildup of fouling and lead to remove the outer tube in that manner. 22 Sparrow Caliber: .22 LR .17 HMR .22 MAG .22 WMR 5.7x28 FN WEIGHT: 6.5 OZ DIAMETER: 1.062" LENGTH: 5.08" FINISH: Black Oxide MATERIALS: Alloy Steel Heat Treated 17-4 PH Stainless Steel Mount: 1/2x28 Threads FEATURES: User Serviceable Multi Part Containment Technology Full Auto Rated on .22 LR O-Ring engagement to keep barrel threads clean and the silencer securely mounted Serialized outer tube is protected Stainless Steel is Chemical and Solvent Resistant Life Warranty

title: For Sale:  SilencerCo Spectre
postcontent:
YOU CAN BUY THIS HERE>SilencerCo Spectre

With its construction of ultra high performance and tough Stainless Steel, the Spectre II allows weapon fire to go virtually unnoticed.

It is not only super tough, but also one of the quietest .22 suppressors known to man. With the Spectre II, users will also enjoy its multi-caliber versatility.

The Spectre II has a unique CTA baffle design for easy disassembly and is user serviceable, which is very important for any .22 lr silencer. Because the .22 lr round is not copper jacketed, molten lead and carbon debris will explode into the silencer when the projectile exits the muzzle. After some time it is possible for a .22 suppressor to fill completely with lead and become heavy an ineffective. To avoid this issue .22 silencers must be able to be disassembled for cleaning regularly maintained. Most .22 silencers on the market can be disassembled for cleaning, however they require cleaning every 50 to 200 rounds or often times they will fuse together and they are unable to come apart. When the lead and carbon debris adhere to the inner wall of the silencer tube and fill the spaces between the baffles and the tube, there is simply too much build up of fouling and lead to remove the tube from most .22 lr silencers on the market. The Spectre II has the unique CTA baffle design that keeps the carbon and lead debris from reaching the silencer tube allowing it to be disassembled easily.

title: For Sale:  SilencerCo Warlock II
postcontent:
YOU CAN BUY THIS HERE>SilencerCo Warlock II

The Warlock II was created for maximum sound suppression in a lightweight aluminum package. The Warlock II has minimal first round pop for optimal discretion. From varmint hunting to plinking, this .22 suppressor will ensure quiet success.

The Warlock II has unique CTA baffle design for easy disassembly and user serviceability, which is very important for any .22 lr silencer. Because the .22 lr round is not copper jacketed, molten lead and carbon debris will explode into the silencer when the projectile exits the muzzle. After some time it is possible for  a .22 suppressor to fill completely with lead and become heavy and ineffective. To avoid this issue they must be disassembled for cleaning and regularly maintained. Most .22 silencers on the market can be disassembled for cleaning, however they require cleaning every 50 to 200 rounds or often times they will fuse together and they are unable to come apart. When the lead and carbon debris adhere to the inner wall of the silencer tube and fill the spaces between the baffles and the tube, there is simply too much build up of fouling and lead to remove the tube from most .22 lr silencers on the market. The Warlock II has the unique CTA baffle design that keeps the carbon and lead debris from reaching the silencer tube allowing it to be disassembled easily.

title: For Sale:  SLR-107UR SLR107-UR 7.62x39 Factory SBR
postcontent:
This is my SLR-107UR. This rifle is a factory SBR and these are pretty hard to come by. This rifle has about 300 rounds through it, but it is in outstanding condition as you can see below. No personal information has been engraved onto this rifle due to the fake can/barrel extension that was attached in lieu of filing for a tax stamp. The barrel extension was cleanly pinned and welded over per ATF requirements. With the right tools, the extension can be easily removed with little evidence that it was ever pinned. Once the extension is removed, no additional gas work will be needed since this was a factory SBR. Let me repeat that... no additional gas work is needed. This rifle is properly gassed for the 8” Krinkov barrel. It runs flawlessly (with or without the extension). Mag lock-up is excellent with little to no movement.

Let me elaborate on the SBR status of this rifle since some of you may not know much about the process. This rifle is NOT currently a SBR and has been removed from the NFA registry since the extension was pinned. This is a legal-length rifle that will ship to your FFL and you can take possession of it immediately. You can then file for your tax stamp and remove the extension once you have your approval paperwork. Lastly, since I have receive quite a few questions on this - this IS a factory SBR. It came as a SBR from K-Var. It was not chopped after being purchased. That is why no gas work was or will be needed.

If I recall correctly, these were right around $2,300 new. Given how scarce these are, I feel that my price is more than fair and I have seen these go for a lot more.  Included, but not pictured are the cleaning kit and oil bottle that came with the rifle. The original box is MIA. The rifle will ship with one US-made polymer mag. You can also see this rifle, where I have it listed on GunBroker.  Feel free to check my feedback.  This rifle will not disappoint.  

Add $40 to my asking price to cover shipping and insurance.  

Lastly, we all know that Armslist is full of scams.  That is no secret.  If you get in contact with me, I will be more than happy to provide more photos.  I will also have no problem shipping through my FFL (add $30 for that) if that will make you more comfortable.  A FTF transaction in PA is also GTG as long as you are a PA resident, willing to fill out a bill of sale and provide identification.
